cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with reservoir computing, a type of neural network, and its design problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of the reservoir model in executing specific tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper addresses the real-time multitasking aspect of the reservoir design problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses the ridge regression estimator to assess the impact of finite sample training on the reservoir capacity. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with the processing of multidimensional input signals using nonlinear memory capacity.
